I am trying to promote my RedBubble store product through Newsbreak, but apparently my ads won't deliver since I have to create an event and paste a pixel to my website (which on RedBubble is not possible). WHat are my options?

Promoting your RedBubble store on NewsBreak can be a bit tricky since RedBubble doesn't allow you to add custom pixels or tracking codes directly to their site. However, you can still run ads without the pixel by focusing on broad targeting and optimizing based on the performance data available through NewsBreak's ad platform. 
If you're looking for more detailed tracking, consider using a landing page that you control, where you can place the pixel and then redirect users to your RedBubble store. This way, you can track conversions from the landing page.
For more information on setting up event tracking and optimizing your campaigns, check out our Event Tracking guide here: [Event Tracking](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/25515090832013-How-to-set-up-a-RedTrack-Postback-on-NewsBreak). Let me know if you have any other questions!
